      "Cuisine": "",
      "Name": "Hash Brown Potato Casserole",
      "Notes": "",
      "Recipe/Ingredients": "Potato Ingredients:\n1 1.75 lb Package of Ore-Ida potatoes O'Brien\n2 cans Camp-bell's cream of Potato soup\n8-ounces sour cream\n8 or 10 or 12 ounces sharp cheddar cheese, grated (does not need to be exact but 10 to 12 is best)\n1 tsp garlic salt (Optional)\n\nTopping:\n\u00bd Cup Parmesan cheese, grated\nButter (about 1 to 2 Tbs, cut into small pieces) (Optional)\nPaprika (Optional)\n\nMix together in a big bowl:\nPackage of Ore-Ida potatoes O'Brien\nCamp-bell's cream of Potato soup\nsour cream\ncheddar cheese\ngarlic salt\n\nInstructions:\nPour into a greased 13 X 9-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.\nCut the butter into about 8-12 little pieces and place on top of the potatoes (this is optional).\nSprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.\nSprinkle a little paprika over top for color.\nBake uncovered at 350F degrees for 1 \u00bd hours.",
